      "description": "The market resolves NO: The 7-day moving average never reaches 60 through June 30, 2026, because traffic remains severely suppressed amid an ongoing crisis and insufficient time for a full rebound.",
      "prior_probability": 0.2,
      "posterior_probability": 0.9,
      "supporting_evidence": ["7-day MA near 4.71 as of May 31, requiring a ~13x surge within ~3 weeks to breach 60 (https://en.macromicro.me/series/30932/imf-hormuz-number-total-ma7)", "Traffic remains near zero with peace talks stalled as of June 5 (https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-06-05/hormuz-tracker-traffic-remains-near-zero-as-peace-talks-stall)", "Strait still effectively closed after three months of paralysis (https://hormuz-traffic.com/)"],
